ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project is part of a larger research-oriented system aimed at Signature Detection using Federated Learning.
The current implementation serves as a baseline machine learning prototype to study classification behavior, decision boundaries, and phase-transitionâ€“like phenomena using logistic regression on synthetic data.

The long-term goal is to:

Replace synthetic data with real signature images

Move from centralized training to Federated Learning (FL)

Ensure data privacy across distributed clients (banks, institutions, devices)

ğŸ§  Motivation

Signature verification systems face two major challenges:

Privacy â€“ signature data is highly sensitive

Generalization â€“ signatures vary across users, time, and conditions

Federated Learning allows training a global model without sharing raw data, making it ideal for signature detection systems deployed across multiple organizations.

This repository currently focuses on:

Understanding binary classification behavior

Analyzing learning dynamics

Preparing the ML pipeline for federated extension

