ğŸ”¹ Data Generation

Synthetic 2D Ising-modelâ€“like lattice data is generated

Each sample represents a binary state matrix

Labels are assigned based on a critical threshold (analogous to phase transition)

This mimics how handwritten signatures can transition between genuine and forged patterns.

ğŸ”¹ Model Architecture

Logistic Regression implemented using PyTorch

Single linear layer + sigmoid activation

Binary classification using Binary Cross Entropy Loss

ğŸ”¹ Training Strategy

Mini-batch gradient descent

Adam optimizer

Train-test split (80/20)

Performance tracked via:

Loss per epoch

Classification accuracy

ğŸ”¹ Visualization & Analysis

The code produces:

Accuracy vs Epoch Plot â€“ learning behavior

Phase Classification vs Temperature Plot â€“ decision boundary analysis

Ordered vs Disordered State Visualization â€“ pattern separation

These visualizations help interpret model confidence and transitions, which is crucial for biometric verification tasks.

ğŸ“Š Results

The model successfully learns a non-random decision boundary

Accuracy improves steadily across epochs

Clear separation between two phases (classes)

This validates the classification pipeline before scaling to federated learning.
